has not been happening.

00:38:36.415 --> 00:38:39.040
And it probably will not happen,
and it's probably a good thing

00:38:39.040 --> 00:38:41.600
that it's not going to happen
in the next couple of years.

00:38:41.600 --> 00:38:43.840
But at some point,
it is inevitable

00:38:43.840 --> 00:38:45.610
that we will have not
just infrastructure

00:38:45.610 --> 00:38:49.840
week but infrastructure era
because the systems that we

00:38:49.840 --> 00:38:52.930
rely on to live
in modern society

00:38:52.930 --> 00:38:54.910
simply don't work anymore.

00:38:54.910 --> 00:38:56.740
And I'm saying that
to a roomful of people

00:38:56.740 --> 00:38:58.810
who probably taking the
subway enough to know

00:38:58.810 --> 00:39:01.030
that that's true.

00:39:01.030 --> 00:39:04.037
But this-- systems where
you pick your system type,

00:39:04.037 --> 00:39:04.870
they're out of date.

00:39:04.870 --> 00:39:07.660
They were built at another
moment with different

00:39:07.660 --> 00:39:08.890
technology .

00:39:08.890 --> 00:39:10.960
They're worn down, and
they're clearly not up

00:39:10.960 --> 00:39:14.290
to the kinds of challenges
we face in the 21st century.

00:39:14.290 --> 00:39:17.740
Currently the biggest
and boldest idea

00:39:17.740 --> 00:39:20.470
for infrastructure that we
have from our government

00:39:20.470 --> 00:39:22.510
is the wall.

00:39:22.510 --> 00:39:25.450
And unfortunately it's also the
most anti-social infrastructure

00:39:25.450 --> 00:39:27.717
that one could possibly imagine.

00:39:27.717 --> 00:39:28.675
It's a losing strategy.

00:39:31.570 --> 00:39:34.770
We also have a vision
for infrastructure

00:39:34.770 --> 00:39:37.010
that comes out of
the tech sector,

00:39:37.010 --> 00:39:39.805
